D3 is a great tool for creating visualizations of your data. That same functionality of bringing your data to life can be used to create visual experiences with randomized data. To get started with simple visualizations using D3 and SVG, first we will create an SVG Container. 

{% highlight javascript linens %}
var body = d3.select('body');

var wall = body.append('svg')
               .attr('width', wallWidth + 15)
               .attr('height', wallHeight + 15)
               .attr('class', 'wall');
{% endhighlight %}

[Click here to see a working example of the final product.](http://waggish-operation.surge.sh/)

